</style></head><body><br><div id="mainContainer"><div id="mainContent"><div class="documentDiv noBg"><div id="docContent"><div id="fullDocument"><div class="tab"><ul id="docToc"><li><a href="#id0-I.">I.</a></li><li><a href="#id1-II.">II.</a></li><li><a href="#id2-III.">III.</a></li><li><a href="#id3-IV.">IV.</a></li><li><a href="#id4-VI.">VI.</a></li></ul><div style="text-align:center; font-weight:bold;" class="stdoc"><p>United Kingdom-Belfast: Compressors</p><p>2019/S 095-230840</p></div><div class="DocumentBody"><div style="text-align:center; font-weight:bold;" class="stdoc"><p>Contract notice &ndash; utilities</p></div><div style="text-align:center; font-weight:bold;" class="stdoc"><p>Services</p></div><div style="text-align:left; font-weight:bold;" class="stdoc">Legal Basis:</div>Directive 2014/25/EU<div class="grseq"><p class="tigrseq"><span id="id0-I."></span>Section I: Contracting entity</p><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->I.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Name and addresses</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Official name: Translink<br>Postal address: Procurement Department<br>Town: Belfast<br>NUTS code: <span class="nutsCode">UK UNITED KINGDOM</span><br>Postal code: BT2 7LX<br>Country: United Kingdom<br>Contact person: neil.bowerstranslink.co.uk<br>E-mail: <a class="ojsmailto" href="mailto:neil.bowers@translink.co.uk?subject=TED">neil.bowers@translink.co.uk</a><p><b>Internet address(es): </b></p><p>Main address: <a class="ojshref" href="https://etendersni.gov.uk/epps" target="_blank">https://etendersni.gov.uk/epps</a></p><p>Address of the buyer profile: <a class="ojshref" href="https://etendersni.gov.uk/epps" target="_blank">https://etendersni.gov.uk/epps</a></p></div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->I.2)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about joint procurement</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->I.3)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Communication</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">The procurement documents are available for unrestricted and full direct access, free of charge, at: <a class="ojshref" href="http://www.etendersni.gov.uk" target="_blank">www.etendersni.gov.uk</a></div><!--//txtmark end--><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Additional information can be obtained from the abovementioned address</div><!--//txtmark end--><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Tenders or requests to participate must be submitted to the abovementioned address</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->I.6)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Main activity</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Urban railway, tramway, trolleybus or bus services</div><!--//txtmark end--></div></div><!--// grseq end--><div class="grseq"><p class="tigrseq"><span id="id1-II."></span>Section II: Object</p><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Scope of the procurement</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.1.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Title:</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark"><p class="p">
<p>Translink &mdash; Maintenance of Air Compression Systems</p>
</p></div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.1.2)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Main CPV code</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark"><span class="cpvCode">42123000 Compressors</span></div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.1.3)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Type of contract</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Services</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.1.4)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Short description:</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark"><p class="p">
<p>Translink carries out engineering maintenance of its fleet (bus and rail) at a number of sites throughout Northern Ireland. The company operates wide range air compression systems for such tasks and wishes to appoint suitable contractors to carry out the maintenance of these systems and also to provide a breakdown repair service, including out of hours calls as and when required.</p>
</p></div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.1.5)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Estimated total value</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.1.6)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about lots</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">This contract is divided into lots: no</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Description</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Title:</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.2)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Additional CPV code(s)</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark"><span class="cpvCode">42124330 Parts of air compressors</span></div><!--//txtmark end--><div style="color:black" class="txtmark"><span class="cpvCode">42123400 Air compressors</span></div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.3)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Place of performance</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">NUTS code: <span class="nutsCode">UKN NORTHERN IRELAND</span></div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.4)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Description of the procurement:</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark"><p class="p">
<p>Translink carries out engineering maintenance of its fleet (bus and rail) at a number of sites throughout Northern Ireland. The company operates wide range air compression systems for such tasks and wishes to appoint suitable contractors to carry out the maintenance of these systems and also to provide a breakdown repair service, including out of hours calls as and when required.</p>
</p></div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.5)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Award criteria</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Price is not the only award criterion and all criteria are stated only in the procurement documents</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.6)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Estimated value</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.7)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Duration of the contract, framework agreement or dynamic purchasing system</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Duration in months: 60</div><!--//txtmark end--><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">This contract is subject to renewal: no</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.10)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about variants</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Variants will be accepted: no</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.11)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about options</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Options: no</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.12)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about electronic catalogues</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.13)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about European Union funds</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">The procurement is related to a project and/or programme financed by European Union funds: no</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->II.2.14)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Additional information</span></div></div><!--// grseq end--><div class="grseq"><p class="tigrseq"><span id="id2-III."></span>Section III: Legal, economic, financial and technical information</p><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Conditions for participation</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.1.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Suitability to pursue the professional activity, including requirements relating to enrolment on professional or trade registers</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.1.2)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Economic and financial standing</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Selection criteria as stated in the procurement documents</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.1.3)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Technical and professional ability</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Selection criteria as stated in the procurement documents</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.1.4)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Objective rules and criteria for participation</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.1.5)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about reserved contracts</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.1.6)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Deposits and guarantees required:</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.1.7)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Main financing conditions and payment arrangements and/or reference to the relevant provisions governing them:</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.1.8)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Legal form to be taken by the group of economic operators to whom the contract is to be awarded:</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.2)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Conditions related to the contract</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.2.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about a particular profession</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.2.2)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Contract performance conditions:</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->III.2.3)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about staff responsible for the performance of the contract</span></div></div><!--// grseq end--><div class="grseq"><p class="tigrseq"><span id="id3-IV."></span>Section IV: Procedure</p><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Description</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.1.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Type of procedure</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Open procedure</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.1.3)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about a framework agreement or a dynamic purchasing system</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.1.4)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about reduction of the number of solutions or tenders during negotiation or dialogue</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.1.6)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about electronic auction</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.1.8)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about the Government Procurement Agreement (GPA)</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">The procurement is covered by the Government Procurement Agreement: no</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.2)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Administrative information</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.2.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Previous publication concerning this procedure</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.2.2)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Time limit for receipt of tenders or requests to participate</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Date: 13/06/2019</div><!--//txtmark end--><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Local time: 15:00</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.2.3)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Estimated date of dispatch of invitations to tender or to participate to selected candidates</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.2.4)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Languages in which tenders or requests to participate may be submitted:</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">English</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.2.6)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Minimum time frame during which the tenderer must maintain the tender</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Tender must be valid until: 11/10/2019</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->IV.2.7)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Conditions for opening of tenders</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Date: 13/06/2019</div><!--//txtmark end--><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Local time: 15:30</div><!--//txtmark end--></div></div><!--// grseq end--><div class="grseq"><p class="tigrseq"><span id="id4-VI."></span>Section VI: Complementary information</p><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->VI.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about recurrence</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">This is a recurrent procurement: no</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->VI.2)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Information about electronic workflows</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->VI.3)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Additional information:</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark"><p class="p">
<p>The Translink Group will incorporate a standstill period at the point information on the award of the contract is communicated to tenderers. That notification will provide full information on the award decision. The standstill period, which will be for a minimum of 10 calendar days, provides time for unsuccessful tenderers to challenge the award decision before the contract is entered into. The Utilities Contracts Regulations 2006 provide for aggrieved parties who have been harmed or are at risk of harm by a breach of the rules to take action in the High Court (England, Wales and Northern Ireland).</p>
</p></div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->VI.4)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Procedures for review</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->VI.4.1)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Review body</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">Official name: See VI.3)<br>Town: Belfast<br>Country: United Kingdom</div><!--//txtmark end--></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->VI.4.2)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Body responsible for mediation procedures</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->VI.4.3)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Review procedure</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->VI.4.4)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Service from which information about the review procedure may be obtained</span></div><div class="mlioccur"><span style="color:black" class="nomark"><!--Non empty span 2-->VI.5)</span><span class="timark" style="font-weight:bold;color:black;">Date of dispatch of this notice:</span><div style="color:black" class="txtmark">15/05/2019</div><!--//txtmark end--></div></div><!--// grseq end--></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>